# .forbidden-words — patterns that must NEVER appear in committed files.
#
# Format: one extended-regex per non-blank non-comment line. Matching is
# case-insensitive. The scanner lives in scripts/check-forbidden-words.sh and
# runs in CI against every changed file.
#
# This upstream list targets the universal cases (real homedir paths, obvious
# credential shapes). Organizations with additional restrictions should
# maintain their own extension list in their internal companion repo — see
# DESIGN §8.1 and §9 for the pattern.

# Absolute home paths that leak a real Unix username.
/home/[a-z][a-z0-9_-]+/

# Mount-style paths that are almost always internal.
/SSD[0-9]+/
/mnt/data[0-9]*/

# Credential shapes (very rough — catches accidental paste).
ghp_[A-Za-z0-9]{20,}
gho_[A-Za-z0-9]{20,}
ghs_[A-Za-z0-9]{20,}
AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}
-----BEGIN (OPENSSH|RSA|EC|DSA) PRIVATE KEY-----
